modules.description: Tracks and displays frames per second (FPS) in a graphical application. It maintains internal counters for elapsed frames and computed FPS values, updating them dynamically over time. The module integrates with Cairo for rendering the current FPS at specified screen coordinates.

This module offers string manipulation via regular expressions, file and buffer operations, and Cairo-based 2D graphics rendering for shapes, text, and images. It manages global state for rendering contexts and image caching, supporting tasks like dynamic visual content generation, interactive canvas applications, and image processing workflows. Key use cases include building graphical interfaces with real-time input handling, rendering scalable vector graphics, and composing image manipulation pipelines with monadic error handling.
